you search through the jobs postings but before applying see if you have connections to the company and ask them to help you network your way in for more tips on how to use linkedin visit http learn linkedin com click here to join the cdc's linkedin group to connect with cdc staff stanford alumni and students linkedin information below is a list of linkedin resources that can be useful in making career connections each resource offers a multitude of advice review each approach to networking and adopt an approach that works for you and your career field of interest linkedin resources and strategies linkedin's 10 official tips to enhance your job search linked intelligence an online library of resources career library resources i m on linkedin now what by jason alba introduces linkedin and the basics of establishing an account and moves on to explain the various tools and functions and how they can be best utilized to help the user find what they want in their social networking the connect effect by michael dulworth explores the personal professional and virtual networks and offers tools strategies and resources to help you make the best use of each one back to top resources & professional associations up guide to informational interviews groups career development center printer friendly version calendar schedule an appointment graphic calendar pages schedule an appointment with a career counselor quick links calendar career fair schedule career planning handbook career library vault guided career path facebook linkedin what is the cdc copyright 2011 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints report a problem with this site
